VThe stock of the Argosy Gaming Company surged yesterday after the company and its joint venture partners said they had secured a certificate to operate a riverboat casino in Lawrenceburg, Ind. The stock rose $3.75, to $16.625, in Nasdaq trading. Argosy said Friday that it expects the 3,400-passenger facility near Cincinnati on the Ohio River to be the nation's largest riverboat casino. Three other stocks -- the Boyd Gaming Corporation, Boomtown Inc. and Ameristar Casinos Inc. -- all fell sharply because they did not get the contract, according to analysts.
