VThe Boyd Gaming Corporation has bought 100 acres in Reno for a $92 million casino, hotel and entertainment complex. The project will be called Sam's Town Reno, according to Boyd, which is based in Las Vegas. It will include a casino, a 211-room hotel, an indoor events center and an outdoor arena. The purchase price of the land was not disclosed. Boyd operates casino-entertainment properties in Nevada, Mississippi, Louisiana and Missouri.
