VThe Boyd Gaming Corporation agreed yesterday to buy the Par-a-Dice Gaming Corporation for $163 million in cash and the assumption of $12 million of debt. Par-A-Dice owns the Par-A-Dice riverboat casino in East Peoria, Ill. Boyd Gaming said it valued the riverboat and land-based assets and operation at $155 million. Boyd is also acquiring an adjacent 204-room hotel and a vacant potential gaming site in Missouri, which the company valued at $20 million. Shares of Boyd Gaming, based in Las Vegas, Nev., rose 50 cents, to $14.
