VTrump Hotels and Casino Resorts said yesterday that it had formally agreed to buy Trump's Castle Casino Resort in Atlantic City from Donald J. Trump for about $525 million. The transaction, which Mr. Trump planned earlier this year, will unite his four casinos in one publicly traded company. Trump Hotels owns the Trump Taj Mahal and Trump Plaza in Atlantic City, and the Trump Indiana riverboat.
