VThe Boyd Gaming Corporation, a casino owner, said profit in the third quarter fell because of lower-than-expected results at its Stardust casino in Las Vegas and Par-A-Dice property in Illinois. Boyd's shares fell 10 percent. Boyd said it had earned 14 cents to 16 cents a share, below net income of 17 cents a year earlier and the 21-cent forecast of analysts surveyed by Thomson First Call.
