VThe Boyd Gaming Corporation, owner of the Stardust Resort in Las Vegas and 10 other casinos, agreed to buy the Blue Chip Casino, a riverboat in Michigan City, Ind., for $273.5 million to enter the Chicago-area gambling market. Boyd will pay $255 million for the riverboat casino and another $18.5 million for a hotel and parking garage that is under construction and will be attached to the casino complex. Closely held Blue Chip, one of five riverboats operating in Indiana along Lake Michigan, has 1,330 slot machines and 58 table games. The casino is about 60 miles from Chicago. Shares of Boyd, which is based in Las Vegas, were up 81.25 cents, to $6.3125.
