VThe Boyd Gaming Corporation, which already owns a 15 percent interest in the Treasure Chest Casino, would buy the remaining 85 percent from a group of about a dozen Louisiana investors, including the majority owner, Robert Guidry. The casino is owned by Treasure Chest L.L.C. Boyd, which operates the casino, would pay $115 million to acquire the 85 percent interest, said Robert Vosbein, lawyer and spokesman for the Louisiana investors. Sale of the casino is contingent upon approval by the Louisiana Gaming Control Board. Boyd, based in Las Vegas, Nev., is a publicly traded company with 14,000 employees. Its shares slipped 12.5 cents, to $5.375.
